- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity class TC0 and computability of arithmetic operations.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions minimization for Σ0b formulas, which can be related to algorithmic complexity.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the totality of iterated multiplication, which can be related to information theory and coding theory.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely but still possible as the paper discusses the properties of arithmetic operations, which can be relevant to cryptography and security.
